 went in the pub, sat alongside of him in the pub, of course kids could go in the pubs then. While he was having a drink - had a glass of lemonade. Then go up the Empire, take us to the Empire. Oh aye, all right like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did he take you often?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No. He was never home too often. Working all tide work see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did he look after you at all when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No. My oldest sister used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh yes. Fridays the bedrooms. And - knives and forks with the knife board then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What would you have to do in the bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Do the floors. And - the other boys, they had little jobs to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What did they have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Scrub the back yard. Chop a bit of wood. All jobs like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What about your sisters, what sort of jobs would they have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Well they had - looking after the other - youngsters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 How long did you continue to do that, did you do it after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Only as long as you were in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Well - 'til I had a little part time job, while I was going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 You had a little job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did the older children help the younger children with things they found difficult, like dressing or eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh yes, oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 And help to look after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Well, if it was necessary.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What about the younger children, would they help the older children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Well, they had nothing to help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh aye, you had to be in. Yes. You had to - oh in fact we was all in bed by nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh - oldest sister used to - see you in bed and tuck you in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did she put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 At what age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh - any age, put myself to bed any time. All do was - shove the clothes back and get in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did you share the bedroom with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Yes. Two brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did you share the bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Two in one bed and one in the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Do you remember how the whole family slept?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Well the girls had a bedroom of their own. And the boys had a bedroom of their own. And the front bedroom 
- the youngest - had a little bed in - you know, where my father and mother slept.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Every Friday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Every tim
e you changed - after your bath. Shirt - shirt, singlet and - all that business. And Welsh flannel shirts. Aye. Oh aye. Good clothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh, not without my mother had - like say her sisters or somebody come there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 You would then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 We were - they'd go in the middle room and have their - and we'd be in the kitchen. Well the table wouldn't be big enough for 'em see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What sort of cooking equipment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh cook anything. We had a - a big range.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No oil or gas stove or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 A coal range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Coal, all coal, aye. And when they had the gas put in we had a gas ring. Stand that on top of the - hob and light that in the morning.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 So you could have it quickly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Cup of - cup of tea. -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Do you remember when you were a little boy? Were all the members of the family there to breakfast, did your father go out first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh he was tide work. Of course you never - sometimes he'd be there, sometimes he wouldn't be there for three or four days like.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 How would he have his breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 He'd have it mostly on his own. My mother'd have her breakfast with us - a lot you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 All of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Aye, we'd be - gone to school probably when he'd get up then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What did you usually have to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh, plenty of grub. Bacon. Sometimes. Porridge. Toast if you wanted it. And sometimes some fish, any fish about we'd have some then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What did you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did you have anything different on certain days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Any what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Anything different for breakfast, say on Sunday or Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No, about the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What about the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh you always had a cooked dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Who would be present at the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Well your mother and your - father may not, he may be out see, tide. But all the rest'd be there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What would you have to eat then for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Plenty of potatoes and - meat was cheap. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12462136\charrsid1668751 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751  sheep}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12462136\charrsid1668751 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 
s head soup sometimes. Sometimes bullocks head. Or a big meat pie, you know, made from the cheek of the cows head. Plenty of boiled Swedes and spuds. Any fruit about you'd have stewed plums and - or apple and custard or something you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What would you have to drink?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Tea I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What about evening, what other meals did you have then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What would you have for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh might have a bit of cake or - cup of tea, cake or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Who would be there to have tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Well all the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Would there be another meal again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 It's all accor
ding to how you were. If you were a good boy you might stop and have a bit of supper, bit of bread and cheese or something. If you wasn't you'd be - upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Was that often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh, very often. It was when you were a - kid
die running about down here - maybe playing in the boats or something or the other you know, you - you'd lose count of time coming home in the night you know, of course you'd have a banging and upstairs, no supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 It must have been a lovely place to have been a child here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 
Different them days to what it is now. There was plenty - of course the canal was here and - all that. Plenty of boats, play with boats. Sailing pilot boats then you know. They was all moored in the Pier}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12462136\charrsid1668751 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 head.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Could you run out freely as children and go and play, wasn't it dangerous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No. There was very little traffic down this part. Very quiet. More traffic now than ever there had been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Yes, my mother used to. Sometimes, not always. 'Cos there was a bakers very near opposite us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh very often. When plums were cheap and - greengages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What about bottled fruit, would she bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Aye, gooseberries. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No, I never known her do vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Would she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh aye, pickled onions, pickled cabbage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Would she make wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Or any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No - what was it we used to have, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12462136\charrsid1668751 sarsaparilla}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751  and - li}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12462136\charrsid1668751 qu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 
orice with it. Made a big jugful of it. When you had colds or - I forget what else was in it. Linseed. You know, some sort of a hash up of - I know you'd got to have a glassful of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did your mother or father grow their own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did they buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 They had to buy it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did they have any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did they keep any livestock for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh chickens - couple of chickens out the back yard we used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 
Well all of us. Perhaps - your father'd be home one day you see - get the shovel and dig the bottom of that coup up you know and - he'd put some - chloride of lime in it - over it and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 You'd all do that would you, the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Well, it's - according to who was there. When you felt like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh very near every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Would you have any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did you ever get some extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did your father have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 He didn't have - he wasn't a great big eater.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Were you allowed to talk during the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh yes. Of course you could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No - no picking and choosing, you had - it was put on your plate, there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Well you can't be well. You was always - plenty hungry. Well we was always good eaters, all good healthy children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 If there was something on the table that you wanted, like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12462136\charrsid1668751 Aye, if it was too far away.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No, no. It - perhaps your brother'd be sat over there like, say pass me the salt, Tom or George or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Yes. Al - always plenty of food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way, and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh no, you sat at the table, you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did you remember how you sat round the table, would you always have the same place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh the - the first in. Sit where you like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh not when the food was on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 
After you'd finished. There was no bed pardon going. No. Oh no. No, you could get up and - go and wash your hands and - whatever you want to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Yes, all the - all that could get around it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Could you all get around it together?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 
Well there was - one little girl always - had to sit in a - a big chair like you know, she had a curvature in her spine, one of the twins. And there was two sat by her, there was two t
he other end and three the other side - oh we - but you - you had no particular spot. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 How was the meal served, who would serve it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 My mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Would she serve it straight from the saucepan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No, dishes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 You had dishes on the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 With the food in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 
Yes. She put it - put it - the spuds all in a big dish. Spoon it out, so many plates, then cabbage or - whatever vegetable it was. And then the meat, and then the gravy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Who would she give it to first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh, to nearest one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Where did they younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Well they always - sat up the top by your - your mother like you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Well one of the other of us that was bigger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What about the woman who came to wash, would she have a meal with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Where would she sit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 She'd sit at the table too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Would she have the same food?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Same exactly. Just the same. Well they were all old. All nei
ghbours like you know, you - you wouldn't think of - treating them different I mean what you were yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh rather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Did she show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Of course she did. Anything the matter with you - sometimes she did with her cane. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 For what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 
Well - don't know what - doing things. There was a stores at back of where we lived, and we used to get over the back wall of it, it was a - hay and corn and all sorts in it. And they used to
 buy stuff from the ships you know, the - all sweepings from the holds, well there'd be monkey nuts and all that in it, well we'd be over there - ripping and tearing your clothes to pieces. And that's when we had a - a walloping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Would your father give you a walloping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No. Never really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Can you remember any particular walloping you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 No, no serious -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 What did you think about having the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Well, I was entitled to it - we didn't never used to take much notice of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14556438 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 If you had any worries could you share them with your mother or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1907356 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13532555\charrsid1668751 Oh yes, of course you could.
